The name,  tape and excellent finish suggests suitability to my needs as a professional accountant. But this fails to deliver what is expected from an "office calculator." That is to handle the precedence of operations and rounding correctly, AND to present FINANCIAL figures to a fixed number of decimal places. Most users do not appreciate the difference,  but it is critical. It must be possible to calculate a ratio to FULL precision, apply that to financial amounts, and THEN round the result.
replyContent: Currently you can achive this only by switching decimal places between floating point for full precision and 2 places to round the result. In the future I will add an option for rounding behaviour which allow to select rounding to occur always / for summands / for result

Two remarks: (1) You can switch on automatically insertion of the decimal point, go to Menu / Settings / Decimal Point Mode - Auto Decimal Point.
(2) Zooming when tripple tapping on the screen is caused by the Magnification gesture of Android and nothing special to my calculator. This must be disabled in the Accessibility Settings of your phone.
